{
  "text": "Contrary to our predictions, impulsivity was associated with more false alarms in the SF/ST condition. Thus, while impulsivity has been linked to poor overall performance on other laboratory tasks of decision making (e.g., [CITATION_1] , the present study found that impulsivity was associated with poor performance specifically in response to sexually arousing stimuli. Some conceptualizations of impulsivity involve a tendency to respond to motivationally-or emotionally-salient stimuli [CITATION_2] , which may explain this finding.",
  "correct_citation": {
